Sponsor my harbour clean-upThis June I will row from California to Hawaii to raise awareness of plastic pollution and to fundraise for our partner SEA CLEANERS (www.seacleaners.com).To fund the row, in which I will spend six weeks rowing 12 hours a day in an eight-metre boat, I’m collecting rubbish from Auckland’s waterways on behalf of companies, groups and individuals. To see what lurks in our seas and its effects, watch the accompanying video.For a $NZ100 donation I’ll remove one 50-litre bag’s worth of litter from locations such as Rangitoto Island, Henderson Creek, Tamaki River, the Shore, or anywhere you want to see cleaned. For $20 you can sponsor a 20 per cent share of a bag.10% of all donations will be given to SEA CLEANERS.For your $NZ100 you will also receive:
A certificate of authentication with a photo of your bag of rubbish;
Your name etched on our transpacific rowing boat, the Britannia 4;

Your name or company name on our Team Pacific Rowers website with public thanks on social media;

A warm, smug feeling that you’ve helped clean up a little part of our beautiful harbour.

Pay for 10 bags of rubbish and in addition receive:
Branding on our transpacific boat, the Britannia 4;
Photographs from the middle of the Pacific;

A warmer, even smugger feeling you have cleaned up lots of the harbour!
